			// "editor.selectionForeground": "#ffffff", // Uncomment to force a fixed text color inside selections if contrast is still poor
			"editor.focusedStackFrameHighlightBackground": "#0000ff", // This is related to Debug? What it is: The full-line highlight on the line where the debugger is currently paused in the active stack frame. You see it constantly when stepping through code with the debugger.
			// Live trigger recipe:
			// Open any script (Python, JS, whatever).
			// Click in the gutter to set a breakpoint (or F9).
			// F5 to start debugging.
			// When execution pauses on the breakpoint, the line gets this highlight.
			// With value at pure #0000ff you can't read the line you're debugging. That's the whole problem.
