			// What it is: Highlights the final tabstop ($0 in snippet syntax) of a snippet — the position your cursor lands at after Tab-ing through all the placeholder fields. Visible for as long as the snippet session is "active" (until you start typing or click away).
			// Live trigger recipe:
			// Open a Python file (you already have Python tooling configured).
			// Type for and pick the for snippet from autocomplete.
			// Tab through index, iterable placeholders.
			// After the last Tab, your cursor lands on the $0 exit point — that's where this highlight appears.
			// Currently #ff0000 opaque — the entire spot becomes a solid red square.
